text: Dumaguete is a city in the Philippines. It is the capital of the province of Negros Oriental. According to the 2020 census, 134,103 people lived there. The city is known for Silliman University, the first Protestant and American university in the country and in Asia. ==Media== ===AM Stations=== *DYWC 801 kHz *DYRM 1134 kHz ===FM Stations=== *DYDN Radyo Sincero 95.9 (DYDN; ABJ Broadcasting Services) Category:Cities in the Philippines Category:Provincial capitals of the Philippines Category:Negros Oriental
